<&| _Base; title => "Jamon Quick Start Mini-Tutorial"; section => "Documentation" &>

<h2>Quick Start Mini-Tutorial</h2>

Create a java file <a class="file" href="JamonQs.java">JamonQs.java</a>:

<pre class="java"><&| /org/jamon/escape/Html &><& JamonQsJava &></&></pre>
Create a Jamon template <a href="QsTemp" class="file">QsTemp</a>:
<pre class="jamon"><&| /org/jamon/escape/Html &><& QsTemp &></&></pre>

Set your classpath:
<&|| _command &>
 <|windows>SET CLASSPATH=.;\path\to\jamon.jar</|>
 <|unix>export CLASSPATH=.:/path/to/jamon.jar</|>
</&>

Process the template:
<&|| _command &>
 <|windows>java org.jamon.TemplateProcessor --destDir=. QsTemp</|>
 <|unix>java org.jamon.TemplateProcessor --destDir=. QsTemp</|>
</&>

Compile everything:
<&|| _command &>
 <|windows>javac JamonQs.java QsTemp*.java</|>
 <|unix>javac JamonQs.java QsTemp*.java</|>
</&>

Run it:
<&|| _command &>
 <|windows>java JamonQs one two three</|>
 <|unix>java JamonQs one two three</|>
</&>

You should see:
<pre class="tty"><% output %></pre>
</&>

<%def _command>
  <%farg windows></%farg>
  <%farg unix></%farg>
<p>
  <span class="system">Windows</span>
  <pre class="tty">C:\JAMONTMP&gt; <& windows &></pre>
  <span class="system">Unix</span>
  <pre class="tty">% <& unix &></pre>
</p>
</%def>
